per League]]: [[2000\u201301 Nationalliga A|2000\u201301]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Fussballdaten|chapuisatstephane}}\n*{{NFT player|pid=6418}}\n*{{FIFA player|157814}}\n*[http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=3436 Switzerland stats at Eu-Football]\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title = Switzerland squads\n| bg = #d81e05\n| fg = white\n|list1 =\n{{Switzerland squad 1994 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Switzerland squad UEFA Euro 1996}}\n{{Switzerland squad UEFA Euro 2004}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Awards\n|bg=gold\n|fg=navy\n|list1=\n{{UEFA Jubilee Awards}}\n{{Swiss Super League top scorers}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chapuisat, Stephane}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Swiss-French people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lausanne]]\n[[Category:Swiss footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Swiss Super League players]]\n[[Category:Swiss Challenge League players]]\n[[Category:FC Lausanne-Sport players]]\n[[Category:Grasshopper Club Z\u00fcrich players]]\n[[Category:BSC Young Boys players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:KFC Uerdingen 05 players]]\n[[Category:Borussia Dortmund players]]\n[[Category:Switzerland international footballers]]\n[[Category:1994 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 1996 players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2004 players]]\n[[Category:Swiss expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Swiss expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Kicker-Torj\u00e4gerkanone Award winners]]\n[[Category:FIFA Century Club]]\n[[Category:UEFA Golden Players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Champions League winning players]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Tweaks.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St%C3%A9phane_Chapuisat"}
{"title_page": "Kristine Froseth", "text_new": "{{short description|American and Norwegian actress and model}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Kristine Froseth<!-- use common name/article title -->\n| image         = Kristine Froseth on Vlogbrothers.jpg\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = Froseth interviewed on [[Vlogbrothers]] about ''[[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|Looking for Alaska]]'' in 2019\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1996|09|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[New Jersey]], U.S.\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = {{Hlist|Actress|model}}\n| years_active  = \n}}\n\n'''Kristine Froseth''' (born 21 September 1996<ref name=\"Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dagbladet.no/kjendis/norske-kristine-22-tar-hollywood-med-storm/70193258 | title=Norske Kristine (22) tar Hollywood med storm |trans-title=Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm |language=Norwegian |first=Linn-Christin |last=Marthinussen |date=11 September 2018|website=[[Dagbladet]] |access-date=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's New Cool Girl\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com.au/celebrity/kristine-froseth-18534 | title=Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's New Cool Girl |first=Natasha|last=Harding|date=11 September 2018|website=Elle (Australia)|access-date=13 September 2018}}</ref>) is an American and Norwegian<ref name=\"Vanity Fair\">{{cite web |last=Smith|first=Krista |date=1 October 2018 |title=How Kristine Froseth Became a Netflix Darling |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/10/kristine-froseth-netflix-interview |website=Vanity Fair |access-date=24 October 2018 }}</ref> actress and model. She is known for playing Kelly Aldrich in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[The Society (TV series)|The Society]]'', Hazel Redfield in the short-lived series Dangerous Freaks, and Alaska Young in the [[Hulu]] series ''[[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|Looking for Alaska]]''.\n\n==Life and career==\nFr\u00f8seth was born in the United States to [[Norwegians|Norwegian]] parents and her early life was spent travelling back and forth between [[Oslo]], Norway and [[New Jersey]] due to her father's work.<ref name=\"Vanity Fair\"/>\n\nShe started modelling after being discovered on a catwalk audition at [[Ski Storsenter]] in Norway,<ref name=\"Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amta.no/kultur-og-underholdning/mote/nyheter/toppmodellen-kristine-20-fra-drobak-med-i-thriller-og-netflix-serie/f/5-3-220893 | title=Toppmodellen Kristine (20) fra Dr\u00f8bak med i thriller og Netflix-serie |trans-title=Top model Kristine (20) from Dr\u00f8bak with thriller and Netflix series |language=Norwegian|first=Mariann Leines|last=Dahle|date=16 May 2018|website=Akershus Amtstidende|access-date=4 November 2018}}</ref> and was also scouted by [[IMG Models]] while in [[New Jersey]] at a local mall fashion show.<ref name=\"W mag\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/kristine-froseth-sierra-burgess-is-a-loser-netflix | title=Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's Next Big Romcom Star of Sierra Burgess Is a Loser |first=Lauren|last=McCarthy|date=22 August 2018|website=W Magazine|access-date=13 September 2018}}</ref> She has modelled for brands such as [[Armani]], [[Juicy Couture]], [[Miu Miu]] and [[H&M]].\n\nHer acting career began when a casting director found her photos and encouraged her to audition for the film adaptation of [[John Green (author)|John Green]]'s novel ''[[Looking for Alaska]]''. This film adaptation was never made. In 2016 she was cast in the pilot for a potential series adaptation of ''[[Let the Right One In (TV series)|Let the Right One In]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/09/let-the-right-one-in-kristine-froseth-cast-eli-tnt-pilot-vampire-1201828738/|title='Let The Right One In': Kristine Froseth Set To Star In TNT Vampire Drama Pilot|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=30 September 2016|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=31 August 2017}}</ref> Froseth began her acting career with the 2017 film ''[[Rebel in the Rye]]''.<ref name=\"Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's New Cool Girl\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/a23007860/kristine-froseth-sierra-burgess-is-a-loser-facts/|title=8 Things to Know About Kristine Froseth from \"Sierra Burgess is a Loser\"|first=Tamara|last=Fuentes|date=6 September 2018|website=Seventeen|access-date=13 September 2018}}</ref> In 2018 she starred in two Netflix movies, ''[[Sierra Burgess Is a Loser]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/01/kristine-froseth-sierra-burgess-is-a-loser-cast-1201879683/|title=Kristine Froseth Joins Class For 'Sierra Burgess Is A Loser'|first=Patrick|last=Hipes|date=6 January 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=31 August 2017}}</ref> and ''[[Apostle (film)|Apostle]]'', and a Sky mini-series, ''[[The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair (miniseries)|The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair]]''.\n\nOn 9 May 2018 it was announced that Hulu would be adapting the [[John Green (writer)|John Green]] novel ''Looking for Alaska'' into an [[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|8-episode limited series]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/hulu-looking-for-alaska-limited-series-josh-schwartz-based-john-green-novel-paramount-tv-1202386880/|title=Hulu Ordering 'Looking For Alaska' Limited Series From Josh Schwartz Based On John Green's Novel From Paramount TV|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=2018-05-10|work=Deadline|access-date=May 10, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> On 30 October 2018, John Green announced Kristine Froseth would be playing Alaska Young, one of the main characters.<ref name=\"AlaskaAnnouncementTweet\">{{cite web |last1=Green |first1=John |title=In the Looking for Alaska hulu series, Alaska will be played by Kristine Froseth, and Miles will be played by Charlie Plummer |url=https://twitter.com/johngreen/status/1057301732584251393 |website=Twitter |accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ Film and television roles\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2013\n|''New Face''\n|Herself\n|Web series by [[Dagbladet|DBTV]] (Norway)<ref name=\"Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xaXjU-7AMO4|title=Trailer: New Face|last=Dagbladet|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[False Alarm (The Weeknd song)|False Alarm]]''\n|The Girl\n|Music video from [[The Weeknd]]\n|-\n|2016\n|''Killing Me To Love You''\n|Girl\n|Music video from [[Vancouver Sleep Clinic]]\n|-\n|2016\n|''Junior''\n|Jess \n|Main role, television series\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Rebel in the Rye]]''\n|Shirley Blaney\n|Film\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Let the Right One In (TV series)|Let the Right One In]]''\n|Eli\n|Unsold television pilot\n|-\n|2018 \n|''[[Sierra Burgess Is a Loser]]''\n|Veronica\n|Direct-to-video film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Apostle (film)|Apostle]]''\n|Ffion\n|Direct-to-video film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair (miniseries)|The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair]]''\n|Nola Kellergan\n|Television miniseries\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Society (TV series)|The Society]]''\n| Kelly\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Prey (2019 American film)|Prey]]''\n| Madeleine\n| Direct-to-video film\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Low Tide]]''\n| Mary\n| Film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tribecafilm.com/filmguide/low-tide-2019|title=Low Tide|website=[[Tribeca Film Festival]]|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Assistant (2019 film)|The Assistant]]''\n| Sienna\n| Film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/harvey-weinstein-assistant-movie-matthew-macfadyen-kristine-froseth-makenzie-leigh-kitty-green-1202591047/|title=Harvey Weinstein Assistant Movie: Matthew Macfadyen, Kristine Froseth & Makenzie Leigh Join Kitty Green Pic|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Andreas|last=Wiseman|date=April 8, 2019|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|Looking for Alaska]]''\n| Alaska Young\n| Limited series<ref name=\"AlaskaAnnouncementTweet\"/>\n|-\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| ''[[Birds of Paradise (upcoming film)|Birds of Paradise]]''\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| Film; ''filming''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/ballet-drama-birds-of-paradise-underway-at-amazon-studios-from-director-sarah-adina-smith-exclusive-1203500976/|title=Ballet Drama \u2018Birds of Paradise\u2019 Underway at Amazon Studios From Director Sarah Adina Smith (EXCLUSIVE)|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Matt|last=Donnelly|date=February 11, 2020|access-date=February 11, 2020}}</ref>\n<!-- Hiding \u2013 all future roles require sourcing\n|2018\n|''[[Prey (upcoming film)|Prey]]''\n|Madeleine\n|Post production\n-->\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDB name|8109082}}\n* {{Models.com}}\n* {{Fashionmodel}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Froseth, Kristine}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Norwegian actresses]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of Norwegian descent]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Female models from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Norwegian female models]]\n[[Category:Norwegian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Norwegian television actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Frogn]]\n\n\n{{Norway-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American and Norwegian actress and model}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Kristine Froseth<!-- use common name/article title -->\n| image         = Kristine Froseth on Vlogbrothers.jpg\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = Froseth interviewed on [[Vlogbrothers]] about ''[[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|Looking for Alaska]]'' in 2019\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1996|09|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[New Jersey]], U.S.\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = {{Hlist|Actress|model}}\n| years_active  = \n}}\n\n'''Kristine Froseth''' (born 21 September 1996<ref name=\"Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dagbladet.no/kjendis/norske-kristine-22-tar-hollywood-med-storm/70193258 | title=Norske Kristine (22) tar Hollywood med storm |trans-title=Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm |language=Norwegian |first=Linn-Christin |last=Marthinussen |date=11 September 2018|website=[[Dagbladet]] |access-date=4 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's New Cool Girl\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com.au/celebrity/kristine-froseth-18534 | title=Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's New Cool Girl |first=Natasha|last=Harding|date=11 September 2018|website=Elle (Australia)|access-date=13 September 2018}}</ref>) is an American and Norwegian<ref name=\"Vanity Fair\">{{cite web |last=Smith|first=Krista |date=1 October 2018 |title=How Kristine Froseth Became a Netflix Darling |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/10/kristine-froseth-netflix-interview |website=Vanity Fair |access-date=24 October 2018 }}</ref> actress and model. She is known for playing Kelly Aldrich in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[The Society (TV series)|The Society]]'', Hazel Redfield in the short-lived series Dangerous Freaks, and Alaska Young in the [[Hulu]] series ''[[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|Looking for Alaska]]''.\n\n==Life and career==\nFr\u00f8seth was born in the United States to [[Norwegians|Norwegian]] parents and her early life was spent travelling back and forth between [[Oslo]], Norway and [[New Jersey]] due to her father's work.<ref name=\"Vanity Fair\"/>\n\nShe started modelling after being discovered on a catwalk audition at [[Ski Storsenter]] in Norway,<ref name=\"Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amta.no/kultur-og-underholdning/mote/nyheter/toppmodellen-kristine-20-fra-drobak-med-i-thriller-og-netflix-serie/f/5-3-220893 | title=Toppmodellen Kristine (20) fra Dr\u00f8bak med i thriller og Netflix-serie |trans-title=Top model Kristine (20) from Dr\u00f8bak with thriller and Netflix series |language=Norwegian|first=Mariann Leines|last=Dahle|date=16 May 2018|website=Akershus Amtstidende|access-date=4 November 2018}}</ref> and was also scouted by [[IMG Models]] while in [[New Jersey]] at a local mall fashion show.<ref name=\"W mag\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/kristine-froseth-sierra-burgess-is-a-loser-netflix | title=Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's Next Big Romcom Star of Sierra Burgess Is a Loser |first=Lauren|last=McCarthy|date=22 August 2018|website=W Magazine|access-date=13 September 2018}}</ref> She has modelled for brands such as [[Armani]], [[Juicy Couture]], [[Miu Miu]] and [[H&M]].\n\nHer acting career began when a casting director found her photos and encouraged her to audition for the film adaptation of [[John Green (author)|John Green]]'s novel ''[[Looking for Alaska]]''. This film adaptation was never made. In 2016 she was cast in the pilot for a potential series adaptation of ''[[Let the Right One In (TV series)|Let the Right One In]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/09/let-the-right-one-in-kristine-froseth-cast-eli-tnt-pilot-vampire-1201828738/|title='Let The Right One In': Kristine Froseth Set To Star In TNT Vampire Drama Pilot|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=30 September 2016|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=31 August 2017}}</ref> Froseth began her acting career with the 2017 film ''[[Rebel in the Rye]]''.<ref name=\"Meet Kristine Froseth, Netflix's New Cool Girl\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/a23007860/kristine-froseth-sierra-burgess-is-a-loser-facts/|title=8 Things to Know About Kristine Froseth from \"Sierra Burgess is a Loser\"|first=Tamara|last=Fuentes|date=6 September 2018|website=Seventeen|access-date=13 September 2018}}</ref> In 2018 she starred in two Netflix movies, ''[[Sierra Burgess Is a Loser]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/01/kristine-froseth-sierra-burgess-is-a-loser-cast-1201879683/|title=Kristine Froseth Joins Class For 'Sierra Burgess Is A Loser'|first=Patrick|last=Hipes|date=6 January 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=31 August 2017}}</ref> and ''[[Apostle (film)|Apostle]]'', and a Sky mini-series, ''[[The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair (miniseries)|The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair]]''.\n\nOn 9 May 2018 it was announced that Hulu would be adapting the [[John Green (writer)|John Green]] novel ''Looking for Alaska'' into an [[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|8-episode limited series]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/hulu-looking-for-alaska-limited-series-josh-schwartz-based-john-green-novel-paramount-tv-1202386880/|title=Hulu Ordering 'Looking For Alaska' Limited Series From Josh Schwartz Based On John Green's Novel From Paramount TV|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=2018-05-10|work=Deadline|access-date=May 10, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> On 30 October 2018, John Green announced Kristine Froseth would be playing Alaska Young, one of the main characters.<ref name=\"AlaskaAnnouncementTweet\">{{cite web |last1=Green |first1=John |title=In the Looking for Alaska hulu series, Alaska will be played by Kristine Froseth, and Miles will be played by Charlie Plummer |url=https://twitter.com/johngreen/status/1057301732584251393 |website=Twitter |accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ Film and television roles\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2013\n|''New Face''\n|Herself\n|Web series by [[Dagbladet|DBTV]] (Norway)<ref name=\"Norwegian Kristine (22) takes Hollywood by storm\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xaXjU-7AMO4|title=Trailer: New Face|last=Dagbladet|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[False Alarm (The Weeknd song)|False Alarm]]''\n|The Girl\n|Music video from [[The Weeknd]]\n|-\n|2016\n|''Killing Me To Love You''\n|Girl\n|Music video from [[Vancouver Sleep Clinic]]\n|-\n|2016\n|''Junior''\n|Jess \n|Main role, television series\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Rebel in the Rye]]''\n|Shirley Blaney\n|Film\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Let the Right One In (TV series)|Let the Right One In]]''\n|Eli\n|Unsold television pilot\n|-\n|2018 \n|''[[Sierra Burgess Is a Loser]]''\n|Veronica\n|Direct-to-video film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Apostle (film)|Apostle]]''\n|Ffion\n|Direct-to-video film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair (miniseries)|The Truth About the Harry Quebert Affair]]''\n|Nola Kellergan\n|Television miniseries\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Society (TV series)|The Society]]''\n| Kelly\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Prey (2019 film)|Prey]]''\n| Madeleine\n| Direct-to-video film\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Low Tide]]''\n| Mary\n| Film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tribecafilm.com/filmguide/low-tide-2019|title=Low Tide|website=[[Tribeca Film Festival]]|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Assistant (2019 film)|The Assistant]]''\n| Sienna\n| Film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/harvey-weinstein-assistant-movie-matthew-macfadyen-kristine-froseth-makenzie-leigh-kitty-green-1202591047/|title=Harvey Weinstein Assistant Movie: Matthew Macfadyen, Kristine Froseth & Makenzie Leigh Join Kitty Green Pic|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Andreas|last=Wiseman|date=April 8, 2019|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Looking for Alaska (TV series)|Looking for Alaska]]''\n| Alaska Young\n| Limited series<ref name=\"AlaskaAnnouncementTweet\"/>\n|-\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| ''[[Birds of Paradise (upcoming film)|Birds of Paradise]]''\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| Film; ''filming''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/ballet-drama-birds-of-paradise-underway-at-amazon-studios-from-director-sarah-adina-smith-exclusive-1203500976/|title=Ballet Drama \u2018Birds of Paradise\u2019 Underway at Amazon Studios From Director Sarah Adina Smith (EXCLUSIVE)|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Matt|last=Donnelly|date=February 11, 2020|access-date=February 11, 2020}}</ref>\n<!-- Hiding \u2013 all future roles require sourcing\n|2018\n|''[[Prey (upcoming film)|Prey]]''\n|Madeleine\n|Post production\n-->\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDB name|8109082}}\n* {{Models.com}}\n* {{Fashionmodel}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Froseth, Kristine}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Norwegian actresses]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of Norwegian descent]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Female models from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Norwegian female models]]\n[[Category:Norwegian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Norwegian television actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Frogn]]\n\n\n{{Norway-actor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toPrey (disambiguation)(link changed toPrey (2019 American film)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kristine_Froseth"}
{"title_page": "John Warne", "text_new": "{{short description|American musician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=May 2010}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = John Warne\n| image                 = RelientK-JohnWarne.jpg\n| caption            = Warne performing with Relient K in 2009\n| image_size            =\n| background = solo_singer\n| birth_name = John Warne\n| alias =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1979|6|27}}\n| death_date =\n| origin = U.S.\n| instrument = Bass guitar, guitar, vocals\n| genre           = [[Christian alternative rock]], [[pop punk]]\n| occupation = Musician\n| years_active = 1996\u2013present\n| label =\n| associated_acts = [[Relient K]], [[Ace Troubleshooter]], [[Guerilla Rodeo]]\n| website = \n}}\n\n'''John Warne''' is an American musician who has been active since 1996. He is best known for being the bassist for the [[Christian rock]] band [[Relient K]]<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p425426/biography|pure_url=yes}}|title=Biography: Relient K|last=Huey|first=Steve|publisher=[[All Media Guide|AMG]]|accessdate=19 May 2010}}</ref> as well as being a founding member of the [[Christian punk]] [[band (music)|band]] [[Ace Troubleshooter]].<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p451416/biography|pure_url=yes}}|title=Biography: Ace Troubleshooter|last=Wilson|first=MacKenzie|publisher=[[All Media Guide|AMG]]|accessdate=19 May 2010}}</ref> His hometown is [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]] and lives in [[Golden, Colorado]].\n\n==Bands==\n\n===Relient K===\n[[File:John Warne with Relient K in 2008.jpg|thumbnail|right|Warne performing with Relient K in 2008]]\nWarne originally started filling in as a [[bassist]] for [[Relient K]] in September 2004, after the then [[bassist]] [[Brian Pittman]] left the band less than a month earlier. Warne joined [[Relient K]] as the full-time [[bassist]] and [[backing vocalist]] in February 2005. He has contributed to four Relient K projects, and on four full-length albums, ''[[Five Score and Seven Years Ago]]'', ''[[Forget and Not Slow Down]]'', ''[[Is for Karaoke]]'', and ''[[Collapsible Lung]]''. He also provided back-up vocals for two songs on Relient K's 2004 album ''[[Mmhmm]]''. Warne also animated the band's [[flash cartoon]], ''Woodland Forest''.\n\n===Ace Troubleshooter===\nWarne was a founding member of the now defunct [[Christian punk]] band [[Ace Troubleshooter]], in which he played guitar and sang lead vocals. The band was active from 1996 to 2004, recording five full-length albums, the first two independently released and the last three released under the record label [[Tooth & Nail Records]] or its affiliate [[BEC Recordings]].\n\n===Guerilla Radio===\nIn 2004 Warne participated in the short-lived band [[Guerilla Rodeo]], playing bass. The band's only record was a three-track [[Extended play|EP]].\n\n==Discography==\n\n; With [[Ace Troubleshooter]]\n* ''Back in the Shootin' Match'' (1996) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''Don't Stop a Rockin''' (1999) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''[[Ace Troubleshooter (album)]]'' (2000) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''[[The Madness of the Crowds]]'' (2002) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''[[It's Never Enough]]'' (2004) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n\n; With Guerilla Rodeo\n* ''Ride, Rope and Destroy'' (2004) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n\nWith [[Relient K]]\n* ''[[Mmhmm]]'' (2004) \u2014 guest vocals on \"More Than Useless\" and \"[[Who I Am Hates Who I've Been]]\"\n* ''[[Apathetic EP]]'' (2005) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n* ''[[Five Score and Seven Years Ago]]'' (2007) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n* ''[[The Bird and the Bee Sides]]'' (2008) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals, wrote and sang \"The Last, the Lost, the Least\"\n* ''[[Forget and Not Slow Down]]'' (2009) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n* ''[[Is for Karaoke]]'' (2011) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n* ''[[Collapsible Lung]]'' (2013) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{RelientK}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Warne, John}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American performers of Christian music]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Minneapolis]]\n[[Category:Relient K members]]\n[[Category:American rock bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male bass guitarists]]\n[[Category:Guitarists from Minnesota]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American bass guitarists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American musician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=May 2010}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = John Warne\n| image                 = RelientK-JohnWarne.jpg\n| caption            = Warne performing with Relient K in 2009\n| image_size            =\n| background = solo_singer\n| birth_name = John Warne\n| alias =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1979|6|27}}\n| death_date =\n| origin = U.S.\n| instrument = Bass guitar, guitar, vocals\n| genre           = [[Christian alternative rock]], [[pop punk]]\n| occupation = Musician\n| years_active = 1996\u2013present\n| label =\n| associated_acts = [[Relient K]], [[Ace Troubleshooter]], [[Guerilla Rodeo]]\n| website = \n}}\n\n'''John Warne''' is an American musician who has been active since 1996. He is best known for being the bassist for the [[Christian rock]] band [[Relient K]]<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p425426/biography|pure_url=yes}}|title=Biography: Relient K|last=Huey|first=Steve|publisher=[[All Media Guide|AMG]]|accessdate=19 May 2010}}</ref> as well as being a founding member of the [[Christian punk]] [[band (music)|band]] [[Ace Troubleshooter]].<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p451416/biography|pure_url=yes}}|title=Biography: Ace Troubleshooter|last=Wilson|first=MacKenzie|publisher=[[All Media Guide|AMG]]|accessdate=19 May 2010}}</ref> His hometown is [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]] and lives in [[Golden, Colorado]].\n\n==Bands==\n\n===Relient K===\n[[File:John Warne with Relient K in 2008.jpg|thumbnail|right|Warne performing with Relient K in 2008]]\nWarne originally started filling in as a [[bassist]] for [[Relient K]] in September 2004, after the then [[bassist]] [[Brian Pittman]] left the band less than a month earlier. Warne joined [[Relient K]] as the full-time [[bassist]] and [[backing vocalist]] in February 2005. He has contributed to four Relient K projects, and on four full-length albums, ''[[Five Score and Seven Years Ago]]'', ''[[Forget and Not Slow Down]]'', ''[[Is for Karaoke]]'', and ''[[Collapsible Lung]]''. He also provided back-up vocals for two songs on Relient K's 2004 album ''[[Mmhmm]]''. Warne also animated the band's [[flash cartoon]], ''Woodland Forest''.\n\n===Ace Troubleshooter===\nWarne was a founding member of the now defunct [[Christian punk]] band [[Ace Troubleshooter]], in which he played guitar and sang lead vocals. The band was active from 1996 to 2004, recording five full-length albums, the first two independently released and the last three released under the record label [[Tooth & Nail Records]] or its affiliate [[BEC Recordings]].\n\n===Guerrilla Radio===\nIn 2004 Warne participated in the short-lived band [[Guerilla Rodeo]], playing bass. The band's only record was a three-track [[Extended play|EP]].\n\n==Discography==\n\n; With [[Ace Troubleshooter]]\n* ''Back in the Shootin' Match'' (1996) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''Don't Stop a Rockin''' (1999) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''[[Ace Troubleshooter (album)]]'' (2000) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''[[The Madness of the Crowds]]'' (2002) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n* ''[[It's Never Enough]]'' (2004) \u2014 lead vocals and guitar\n\n; With Guerilla Rodeo\n* ''Ride, Rope and Destroy'' (2004) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n\nWith [[Relient K]]\n* ''[[Mmhmm]]'' (2004) \u2014 guest vocals on \"More Than Useless\" and \"[[Who I Am Hates Who I've Been]]\"\n* ''[[Apathetic EP]]'' (2005) \u2014 bass guitar and backing vocals\n